'''Berrymans Lace Mawer LLP''' is a British law firm with a focus on dispute resolution and insurance.<ref>http://www.legal500.com/firms/317-berrymans-lace-mawer-llp/offices/44-london/profile ''The Legal 500 2010'' firm profile</ref> The firm is ranked 43rd in the [[List of largest UK law firms|list of largest law firms]] by revenue in the United Kingdom compiled by [[The Lawyer]].<ref>http://www.thelawyer.com/directory/uk-200-table-top-100/</ref>

BLM provides legal services in 50 areas of law, grouped into nine market sectors: construction and property, corporate risks, healthcare, insurance and indemnity, leisure, media and technology, public sector, retail and transport.<ref>http://www.chambersandpartners.com/UK/Firms/501-38909 ''Chambers & Partners 2010'' firm profile</ref>

BLM has nine offices, which are situated in Birmingham, Bristol,<ref>http://www.thelawyer.com/berrymans-launches-in-bristol-with-double-partner-hire/1003959.article ''The Lawyer'' - 20 March 2010 'Berrymans launches in Bristol with double partner hire'</ref> Cardiff,<ref>http://www.legalweek.com/legal-week/news/1180106/national-firm-berrymans-surprise-cardiff-debut ''Legal Week'' - 29 October 2007 'National firm Berrymans in surprise Cardiff debut'</ref> Leeds, Liverpool, London, Manchester, Southampton and Stockton-on-Tees. The firm has approximately 1,160 staff including 130 partners.<ref>http://www.chambersandpartners.com/UK/Firms/501-38909</ref>

==History==

The current firm is the result of the 1997 merger of Berrymans with Lace Mawer.<ref>http://www.thelawyer.com/span-id=red20-years-of-the-lawyer/span-1997/130265.article ''The Lawyer'' 20-years-of-the-lawyer - 5 December 2007</ref> The origins of the firm date back to the 18th century, when Joshua Lace gave his name to an already established law firm in Liverpool. In 1901, Frederic Berryman began the practice of Berrymans in the City of London and, in 1946, Arthur Mawer founded AW Mawer & Co in Manchester. Terry Renouf has been the national senior partner since 2006.<ref>http://www.thelawyer.com/berrymans-elects-new-senior-partner/117572.article ''The Lawyer'' 'Berrymans elects new senior partner' - 9 November 2005</ref>
==Corporate social responsibility==

Each BLM office has its own [[corporate social responsibility]] (CSR) programme and representative.<ref>http://www.psmg.co.uk/member_knowledge.cfm?id=1083 ''PSMG'' CSR at Berrymans Lace Mawer</ref>  In January 2007, BLM partnered with [[The Prince's Trust]] for four years, assisting in its support of 14<U+2013>30 year olds to offer practical support including training, mentoring and financial assistance.<ref>http://www.princes-trust.org.uk/about_the_trust/roll_of_patrons.aspx Roll of Patrons 2010</ref>

